While historically near a 50/50 split, NFL teams are running the ball within the 10-yard line just 45% of the time in 2022 so far.

As @DannyBKelly mentioned on today's Ringer Fantasy pod, this is a big reason why RB fantasy production has been so poor this year.

#nfl week 5 begins tonight, so let's check in on how my model views the current state of the league #nflverse
This week, the model feels *very* good about the Bills spoiling @kennypickett10 @steelers debut - let's hope Kenny surprises everyone!  Happy week 5 everyone #nflverse #RStats https://t.co/kiSXyhRAn1

Week 5 of the #nfl is behind us...and the @Steelers are officially bad ðŸ˜¢.  My model has dropped them to under 6 wins and into the driver's seat for next year's first pick.  Dark days indeed.  My model is very bullish on @BuffaloBills with 1/3 sims ending with a SB win #nflverse https://t.co/XIpn04PIjZ

Hereâ€™s our rookie snap counts for 2022. Offense and Defense only. Special teams remains a conspiracy theory, and I refuse to cave, even after the Colts beat KC largely due to them. 

#nflverse #rstats #gtExtras https://t.co/tIZnwMacqx

Here are the defenses. Again, green is good and purple is bad. Note that since this is the defense, negative epa numbers are good, since that essentially measures how likely the offense is to score. 

#nflverse #rstats #ggplot2 https://t.co/xODTcS8ZcD

Snaps by formations for KC vs LV! KC still in mostly 11 personnel, with some 12 mixed in. We are just so much better with 3 WR's on the field (this is a Skyy tweet). On defense, we mixed it up a lot. Really good in 3-4-4. Not good in 3-2-6 (dime?)

#nflverse #rstats #gtExtras https://t.co/5bJBXLFEnS

The "gold standard" that's quoted for Rookie WRs is >2.00 YPRR on >200 routes

Given we're only 5 weeks into the season, YPRR is prone to increased noise. Using data from the ffverse, #nflverse & @KeepTradeCut  here is Expected Rec Yards Per Pass Snap https://t.co/5rstsVav1o

Targeted air yards distributions for the four most targeted players on each team entering Week 5

Data: #nflverse https://t.co/wo2tYj4Uq4

Still waiting on MNF, but here are RB snaps by pass likelihood percentile from the other Week 5 games

Data: #nflverse https://t.co/voSfZpa52X

What the fuck am I seeing ?!?!? 
Rushing epa is higher then passing epa in the first 5 week?!?!??

#nflverse https://t.co/xCFE3yir6u

For @haleyeenglish17, Mahomes he faced more man coverage in the whole league and this year they are back to blitz him ...yes... Why?

#nflverse https://t.co/UOE9HNkmKQ
The only 3 QBs who rank top 10 in EPA in 2021 and 2022 using #nflverse data are Patrick Mahomes, Justin Herbert and Jimmy G

How fast can they be?

Let's see how long each QB takes to throw the ball!

As expected, Brady is fast, at least throwing passes!

Pass Rush Preview!! It's the heavyweight matchup of the regular season. Kansas City vs Buffalo. Both teams are pretty effective against the blitz. Buffalo gets blitzed a bit more often. I highly recommend not blitzing the Chiefs when they are in 3 WR sets. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/2rIBprC9OB

Here are the defenses. Chiefs are most effective when they've blitzed on first downs. Their 4th down numbers are skewed by a Carr to Adams TD thrown on a 4th and 1. Small sample size there. Bills are pretty effective with their blitzes, but don't blitz often.

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/XPFEre346F
